### Request Flow Architecture

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User Browser
    participant R as React Frontend
    participant A as Axios Interceptor
    participant E as Express Server
    participant V as Validator Middleware
    participant RL as Rate Limiter
    participant DB as MongoDB Atlas

    Note over U,DB: SIGNUP FLOW
    U->>R: Fill form + Select role
    R->>R: Client-side validation
    R->>A: POST /api/auth/signup
    A->>A: Attach Bearer token (if exists)
    A->>E: HTTP Request
    E->>RL: Check rate limit (50/15min)
    RL->>V: Pass to validators
    V->>V: Sanitize + Validate all fields
    V->>E: Validation result
    E->>DB: Check duplicate email/username
    DB-->>E: Results
    E->>DB: User.create() — triggers pre('save') hook
    Note over DB: bcrypt.hash(password, 12 rounds)
    DB-->>E: Created user document
    E->>E: user.generateToken() — JWT signed
    E-->>U: 201 { success, token, user }
    U->>R: Store token in localStorage + cookie
    R->>R: getRoleRedirectPath(role)
    R->>U: Navigate to role-specific dashboard
```

