## 4. Database Schema Design

### User Collection Schema

```javascript
// server/models/User.js — Mongoose Schema
const userSchema = new mongoose.Schema({
  fullName:     { type: String, required: true, trim: true, minlength: 2, maxlength: 50 },
  username:     { type: String, required: true, unique: true, trim: true, lowercase: true,
                  minlength: 3, maxlength: 30, match: /^[a-zA-Z0-9_]+$/ },
  email:        { type: String, required: true, unique: true, trim: true, lowercase: true,
                  match: /^\S+@\S+\.\S+$/ },
  password:     { type: String, required: true, minlength: 6, select: false },
  role:         { type: String, required: true,
                  enum: ['cashier', 'kitchen', 'customer', 'manager'], default: 'customer' },
  phone:        { type: String, trim: true, default: '' },
  businessName: { type: String, trim: true, default: '' },
  employeeId:   { type: String, trim: true, default: '' },
  avatar:       { type: String, default: '' },
  isActive:     { type: Boolean, default: true },
  lastLogin:    { type: Date, default: null },
}, { timestamps: true });
```

### Schema Field Reference Table

| Field | Type | Required | Unique | Default | Validation | Security Note |
|-------|------|:--------:|:------:|---------|-----------|--------------|
| `fullName` | String | ✅ | ❌ | — | 2-50 chars, trimmed | Displayed to users |
| `username` | String | ✅ | ✅ | — | 3-30 chars, `[a-zA-Z0-9_]`, lowercased | Unique index |
| `email` | String | ✅ | ✅ | — | Regex `^\S+@\S+\.\S+$`, lowercased | Unique index |
| `password` | String | ✅ | ❌ | — | Min 6 chars, **select: false** | Never returned in queries |
| `role` | String | ✅ | ❌ | `customer` | Enum: cashier\|kitchen\|customer\|manager | Controls RBAC |
| `phone` | String | ❌ | ❌ | `''` | Trimmed | Customer role field |
| `businessName` | String | ❌ | ❌ | `''` | Trimmed | Manager role field |
| `employeeId` | String | ❌ | ❌ | `''` | Trimmed | Cashier/Kitchen field |
| `avatar` | String | ❌ | ❌ | `''` | — | Future profile image |
| `isActive` | Boolean | ❌ | ❌ | `true` | — | Soft-delete mechanism |
| `lastLogin` | Date | ❌ | ❌ | `null` | — | Updated on each login |
| `createdAt` | Date | Auto | ❌ | Auto | Mongoose timestamps | Audit trail |
| `updatedAt` | Date | Auto | ❌ | Auto | Mongoose timestamps | Audit trail |

### Database Indexes

| Index | Fields | Type | Purpose |
|-------|--------|------|---------|
| `_id` | `_id` | Primary (auto) | Document identification |
| `email_1` | `email` | Unique (via schema) | Fast login lookup + duplicate prevention |
| `username_1` | `username` | Unique (via schema) | Fast login lookup + duplicate prevention |
| `role_1` | `role` | Standard (explicit) | Role-based queries in reports |

### MongoDB Atlas Configuration

```
Connection: mongodb+srv://<user>:<password>@cluster0.wiwdr6p.mongodb.net/odoo_pos_cafe
Database:   odoo_pos_cafe
Collection: users
Cluster:    M0 Free Tier (sufficient for hackathon)
Region:     Auto-selected by Atlas
```

> [!CAUTION]
> MongoDB URI is stored exclusively in `server/.env`. It is NEVER exposed to the frontend or committed to version control.

