## 5. API Reference

### API Endpoint Table

| # | Method | Endpoint | Access | Rate Limited | Description |
|---|--------|---------|--------|:------------:|-------------|
| 1 | `POST` | `/api/auth/signup` | Public | ✅ 50/15min | Register new user with role |
| 2 | `POST` | `/api/auth/login` | Public | ✅ 50/15min | Authenticate via email/username |
| 3 | `GET` | `/api/auth/me` | Private | ✅ | Get current authenticated user |
| 4 | `POST` | `/api/auth/logout` | Private | ✅ | Clear auth cookie |
| 5 | `GET` | `/api/auth/check-username/:username` | Public | ✅ | Check username availability |
| 6 | `GET` | `/api/auth/check-email/:email` | Public | ✅ | Check email availability |
| 7 | `GET` | `/api/health` | Public | ❌ | Server health check |

### POST `/api/auth/signup` — User Registration

**Request Body:**

```json
{
  "fullName": "Deep Patel",
  "username": "deeppatel",
  "email": "deep@example.com",
  "password": "Secure@123",
  "confirmPassword": "Secure@123",
  "role": "manager",
  "phone": "+91 9876543210",
  "businessName": "Deep's Cafe",
  "employeeId": ""
}
```

**Server-Side Validation Chain:**

| Field | Rule | Error Message |
|-------|------|--------------|
| `fullName` | `trim().notEmpty().isLength({min:2, max:50})` | "Full name is required" / "Name must be 2-50 characters" |
| `username` | `trim().notEmpty().isLength({min:3, max:30}).matches(/^[a-zA-Z0-9_]+$/)` | "Username is required" / "3-30 characters" / "Letters, numbers, underscores only" |
| `email` | `trim().notEmpty().isEmail().normalizeEmail()` | "Email is required" / "Please enter a valid email" |
| `password` | `notEmpty().isLength({min:6})` | "Password is required" / "Must be at least 6 characters" |
| `confirmPassword` | `notEmpty().custom(value === req.body.password)` | "Please confirm your password" / "Passwords do not match" |
| `role` | `notEmpty().isIn(['cashier','kitchen','customer','manager'])` | "Please select a role" / "Invalid role selected" |

**Success Response (201):**

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIs...",
  "user": {
    "_id": "661f...",
    "fullName": "Deep Patel",
    "username": "deeppatel",
    "email": "deep@example.com",
    "role": "manager",
    "phone": "",
    "businessName": "Deep's Cafe",
    "employeeId": "",
    "isActive": true,
    "lastLogin": null,
    "createdAt": "2026-04-04T08:00:00.000Z",
    "updatedAt": "2026-04-04T08:00:00.000Z"
  }
}
```

**Error Responses:**

| Status | Condition | Response |
|--------|-----------|----------|
| `400` | Validation failure | `{ success: false, message: "...", errors: [...] }` |
| `400` | Duplicate email | `{ success: false, message: "An account with this email already exists", field: "email" }` |
| `400` | Duplicate username | `{ success: false, message: "This username is already taken", field: "username" }` |
| `429` | Rate limited | `{ success: false, message: "Too many requests. Please try again in 15 minutes." }` |
| `500` | Server error | `{ success: false, message: "Server error. Please try again." }` |

### POST `/api/auth/login` — User Login

**Request Body:**

```json
{
  "login": "deep@example.com",
  "password": "Secure@123"
}
```

> [!NOTE]
> The `login` field accepts **both email and username**. The server performs a dual-field `$or` query against both `email` and `username` fields, both lowercased for case-insensitive matching.

**Critical Implementation — Dual-Field Login Query:**

```javascript
// server/routes/auth.js — Line 171-176
const user = await User.findOne({
  $or: [
    { email: login.toLowerCase() },
    { username: login.toLowerCase() },
  ],
}).select('+password');  // ← Explicitly include password for comparison
```

**Login Error Responses:**

| Status | Condition | Response |
|--------|-----------|----------|
| `401` | User not found | `"Invalid credentials — user not found"` |
| `401` | Wrong password | `"Invalid credentials — incorrect password"` |
| `403` | Account deactivated | `"Account is deactivated. Contact your administrator."` |
| `500` | Server error | `"Server error. Please try again."` |

